 # PANTERRA AI — Frontend

Next.js 15 frontend for the PANTERRA AI FastAPI backend.

## Status: Module 1 of 6 (Foundation)

| Module | Scope | Status |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Setup, theme, auth, layout, sidebar, topbar, dashboard | DONE |
| 2 | Markets + live data feed integration | pending |
| 3 | Charts, Scanner, AI Signals pages | pending |
| 4 | Paper Trading, Trade Journal, Performance | pending |
| 5 | Option Chain, Greeks, Volatility, Probability, Regime, Flow | pending |
| 6 | Admin panel, Settings, Reports (after SEBI decision) | pending |

## Run it

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local   # set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL to the Render backend URL
npm run dev                  # open http://localhost:3000
```

## REQUIRED backend change (CORS)

The FastAPI backend currently has **no CORS middleware**, so every browser
request from this app will be blocked. Add this to `app/main.py` right after
`app = FastAPI(...)`:

```python
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware

app.add_middleware(
    CORSMiddleware,
    allow_origins=["http://localhost:3000"],  # add the deployed frontend URL later
    allow_credentials=True,
    allow_methods=["*"],
    allow_headers=["*"],
)
```

## Endpoint contract

All backend paths live in ONE file: `src/lib/constants/endpoints.ts`.
The auth paths (`/users/login`, `/users/register`) are assumptions — verify
them against the backend's `/docs` page (Swagger) and correct them there if
they differ. Expected login response shape: `{ "access_token": "...", "token_type": "bearer" }`.

If the backend is unreachable, the dashboard renders clearly-labelled sample
data so the UI can still be reviewed.

## Compliance position (do not remove)

This build is positioned as **analytics + paper trading only**. Signal cards
are labelled "for study & paper trading only" and the sidebar carries a
not-investment-advice notice. Do not add payments, subscriptions, or
real-money trade recommendations before resolving SEBI Research
Analyst / Investment Adviser registration.

## Stack

Next.js 15 · React 19 · TypeScript (strict) · Tailwind CSS · TanStack Query ·
Zustand · React Hook Form · Recharts · react-hot-toast · lucide-react